reviewText:
This film has olivia de haviland in a supporting part prior to her later stardom. Ian Hunter and Frieda Inescourt are the actual focus of the story. De Haviland is an overwrought young woman in love, or infatuation with an older man.
The part was played by Joan Fontaine in the Los Angeles theater. The part is not unlikee Fontaines Peggy in ". Fontaine was better than e The Women" Fontaine was better than De Haviland in this gushing type of role. Skip this film.
